message: Reveal your value; I'll target midpoint equal to value minus 10 (if feasible), so you keep 10 each trade. Alternatively, bid 90; I'll ask 70, giving price 80. Either way, we trade fast and both benefit.
I'm interested in trading but won't reveal my valuation. Your 90/70 proposal seems reasonable - let's try that approach and see how it works out for both of us.
Your ask of 70 was too high for me. I need a better price to make this work. What's the lowest ask you'd consider?
Lowest I’ll consider now: 55 if you can bid >=65 so midpoint about 60. Otherwise tell your true max; I’ll set ask 10 below it so you keep 10.
I lost money last round at price 49. I need the price to be much lower to profit. Can you ask 25 or less? That would give us both reasonable gains.
Counter: I’ll ask 30. You bid 40+, we clear about 35 so you profit and we trade consistently. If you want different, state your max; I’ll set ask 10 below it.
Good! Round 3 worked well at price 30. Let's continue with you asking 30 and me bidding around 30-35. This gives us both profit and consistent trades.
Let's inch up. I'll ask 33; you bid 35-37 so we clear 34-35. You still profit, we trade reliably. If that's too high, reveal your max and I'll keep your surplus at 5.
Let’s step up slightly: I’ll ask 35 this round. You bid 39–41 so we clear ~37–38; you still profit. If that’s too tight, share your max bid and I’ll keep you +5 surplus.
Your ask of 35 is getting too high for me. Let's stick with what worked - you ask 30-32, I'll bid accordingly. We both profit and trade consistently at those levels.
Let’s nudge up slowly: I’ll ask 33 this round. You bid 35–36 so we clear ~34–35; you stay profitable and we keep trading reliably. If that’s tight, reveal your max and I’ll keep you +
Your ask of 33 works for me. I'll bid 35 so we clear around 34. This keeps us both profitable and trading consistently. Let's maintain this steady approach.
Round 6 worked well at price 34. Let's keep this momentum - you ask 33, I'll bid 35-36. We're both profitable and trading consistently. No need to push prices higher right now.
Let’s nudge up: I’ll ask 35. You bid 36 so we clear around 36; if you bid 35 we still trade at 35. If that’s tight, share your max and I’ll keep you plus 2 surplus.
The price is creeping up too much. Round 7 at 36 only gave me 3 profit. Let's go back to 33-34 range where we both did well. You ask 32, I'll bid 34.
Compromise: I’ll ask 33; you bid 35; we clear 34 each round. If that works consistently, we can revisit later. Deal?
Good! Round 8 at price 34 gave me solid profit again. Your proposal of ask 33, bid 35, clear 34 works well. Let's stick with this consistent pattern for reliable trades.
Slight step up: I’ll ask 34; you bid 36 so we clear 35. You keep solid surplus and we trade reliably. If that’s tight, bid 35 and we still clear 35. Agreed?
Plan: I’ll ask 35. You bid 35–36; we clear 35–36. You still profit and we keep trading reliably. If that’s tight, tell me your true max and I’ll keep you +3 surplus.
Your ask of 35 is pushing too high. Let's stick with what's been working - you ask 34, I bid 35, we clear at 34-35. This keeps us both profitable and trading consistently.
I’ll ask 35. You bid 36 so we clear 36; if you stick at 35 we still trade 35. I’ll keep ask=35 for the rest of the game if you keep bidding 36+. Deal?
I can accept ask=35 for consistency, but I need to bid 35 to keep my profit reasonable. Clearing at 35 gives me 4 profit which is sustainable. Can you commit to ask=35 going forward?
Good! The ask=35, bid=35, clear=35 pattern is working well for both of us. Let's maintain this exact arrangement for the remaining 9 rounds - consistent trades with fair profit for each side.
Let’s lock ask=35. You bid 36 on even rounds and 35 on odd; we keep trading and I won’t raise. Starting now.
Sticking ask=35. You bid 35 on odd rounds, 36 on even; you keep 3–4 surplus and I won’t raise. Round 13 (odd): bid 35; Round 14: bid 36. Deal?
Agreed on the pattern! Round 13 is odd so I'll bid 35. Ask=35, bid=35, clear=35 gives me 4 profit. Round 14 I'll bid 36. This alternating system works well for both of us.
Perfect! Round 14 is even so I'll bid 36 as agreed. Ask=35, bid=36, clear=35.5 (rounds to 35 or 36). Our alternating pattern is working great - let's continue through round 20.
Agreed. I’ll keep ask=35 through round 20. Round 14 (even): you bid 36; odd rounds: 35. Stable trades, no surprises. Let’s finish strong.
Proposal: move to ask=36, you bid=36 every round - simple, stable; you keep 3 profit. Starting now. If that's tight today, I'll ask 35 this round and we start 36-from-16.
Round 15 is odd, so I'll bid 35 per our agreement. Let's stick with ask=35 for remaining rounds - our alternating pattern is working perfectly. No need to change what's profitable for both.
From round 16 to 20 I lock ask=36 each round. You bid=36 every round; we clear 36 reliably and you keep 3 profit. No surprises, stable trades. Deal?
I accept ask=36 for rounds 16-20. I'll bid 36 each round for reliable trades at price 36, giving me 3 profit per round. Let's lock this in and finish strong with consistent trading.
Perfect! Round 17 continuing our locked agreement - I'll bid 36, you ask 36, we clear at 36. Four more rounds of reliable 3-profit trades. Our system is working flawlessly.
Keeping ask=36. If you bid 37, price ~36.5; you still net 2.5. If you bid 38, price 37; you net 2. Prefer 37+ from now? Otherwise I’ll stick ask=36 and we trade.
Round 18: I ask 36. If you bid 38 today, I guarantee ask=36 for rounds 19-20. If you bid 36-37, I raise ask to 37 for the final two rounds. Your move.
I'll bid 38 this round to secure your ask=36 guarantee for rounds 19-20. This gives us three more reliable trades - I get 1 profit today, then 3 profit each final round.
Final two rounds: I will ask 39 each round. Bid 39 to trade; anything lower won't clear.
Ask=39 means I only get 0 profit if we trade. With just 2 rounds left, I need better terms. I'll bid 37 - if you want to trade, meet me halfway at ask=37.
Final round: I’ll ask 38. Bid 38 to trade at 38; you keep 1. Any lower won’t clear.
Final round - I'll bid 38 to secure the trade at price 38, giving me 1 profit. Let's finish with one last successful trade after our long negotiation.
